# 🗄️ DB-3NGIN3 for Linux

A DBngin-style local database manager for Ubuntu / Linux.
Manage PostgreSQL, MySQL, MariaDB, Redis, and MongoDB from a clean dark web UI — no config files, no dependencies beyond Docker.

---

## Quick start

```bash
python3 db3ngin3.py
```

Opens automatically at **http://127.0.0.1:7734**

---

## Requirements

| Requirement | Notes |
|---|---|
| Python 3.8+ | Standard library only — no pip installs |
| Docker | Used to run all database containers |

### Install Docker on Ubuntu

```bash
curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com | sh
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
# Log out and back in, then run db3ngin3.py
```

---

## Supported databases

| Database   | Versions          | Default port | User     | Password |
|------------|-------------------|--------------|----------|----------|
| PostgreSQL | 13, 14, 15, 16    | 5432         | postgres | postgres |
| MySQL      | 5.7, 8.0, 8.3     | 3306         | admin    | admin    |
| MariaDB    | 10.6, 10.11, 11.3 | 3307         | root     | root     |
| Redis      | 6.2, 7.0, 7.2     | 6379         | —        | —        |
| MongoDB    | 5.0, 6.0, 7.0     | 27017        | admin    | admin    |

---

## Features

- **One-click start / stop** — launches Docker containers on demand
- **Persistent data** — database files survive container restarts, stored in `~/.db3ngin3/data/`
- **Auto status sync** — live Docker state polled every 15 seconds
- **Connection strings** — click any instance to expand; copy the connection string in one click
- **Port conflict detection** — prevented at creation time
- **Collapsible sidebar** — full mobile/responsive support
- **No pip dependencies** — pure Python standard library

---

## Data locations

| What | Where |
|---|---|
| Instance metadata | `~/.db3ngin3/instances.json` |
| Database files    | `~/.db3ngin3/data/<instance-id>/` |

Deleting an instance removes the Docker container but keeps data files on disk.

---

## Running as a background service (optional)

```bash
# systemd unit — save as ~/.config/systemd/user/db3ngin3.service
[Unit]
Description=DB-3NGIN3 database manager

[Service]
ExecStart=/usr/bin/python3 /path/to/db3ngin3.py
Restart=on-failure

[Install]
WantedBy=default.target
```

```bash
systemctl --user enable --now db3ngin3
```
